message.raw:
There is really an issue with contact depth in trimesh_sphere. There was a change in depth calculation couple months ago. I didn't find it very good because it introduced discontinuities. Now I have tried the svn trunk version and found there was also a real bug introduced by this change (quite difficult to see at first glance but "side" value isn't actually distance of sphere and triangle plane).
So I changed it to following: depth is calculated as triangle-sphere penetration depth projected to triangle (=contact) normal. This is still just approximation but I find it better than previous two implementations. Also reorganized a bit the code to pull out duplicate calculations. Checked in svn trunk.

- http://q12.org/pipermail/ode-cvs/2005-July/000193.html
- http://q12.org/pipermail/ode-cvs/2005-July/000194.html

explicitly declare that we're using GCC for appropriate platforms, instead of trying to unreliably detect it. otherwise we'd miscompile opcode.

message.raw:
Replaced dRandInt implementation as suggest by [1].
This also fixes a bug encountered by [2], where dRandInt would return
a value greater than N (it should return a value between 0 and N-1).

[1] http://q12.org/pipermail/ode/2005-May/015834.html
[2] http://q12.org/pipermail/ode/2005-June/016143.html
